The paper proposes a deep learning framework for traffic forecasting using spatio-temporal graph convolutional networks. The paper involves the use of deep learning techniques and graph convolutional networks, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for prediction tasks, which is also associated with the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
